<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-2484] performance issue with collections operations when numbers are elements of the collections</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-2484</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In DefaultGroovyMethods.java, a NumberAwareComparator mimics the groovy &apos;==&apos; operator to compare elements against each other for collections operations such as unique(), minus(), sort() etc.&lt;br/&gt;
This NumberAwareComparator systematically converts any number to BigDecimal if numbers are involved slowing down very significantly those operations.&lt;br/&gt;
By testing first if the elements are comparable and of the same &apos;kind&apos; to first compareTo() them, we get a cheap but noticeable boost.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
